For compiling on Linux, go into the gcc folder and run 'make' then go back to this folder and run the executable.

For compiling on Windows, go into the vs folder and use the .sln file provided.

All source files are in the src folder.

You may need to copy glut32.dll/glew32.dll into the Debug/Release folders that visual studio creates if you're on Windows.

All source/header files are provided in the src folder.
